<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Challenge 5: Log Detective</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
</head>
<body>
  <div class="challenge-page">
    <a href="/" class="back-link">← Back to Challenges</a>
    <img src="/images/logo.png" alt="EECS Girls Who Tech Camp" class="page-logo">

    <div class="challenge-header">
      <h1>📋 Challenge 5: Log Detective</h1>
      <p class="desc">A server was attacked! Can you spot the hacker's trail in these logs?</p>
    </div>

    <div class="challenge-content">
      <div class="story-box">
        The web admin noticed weird activity and pulled the server logs. Every request anyone makes gets recorded here. One of these requests has a <strong>secret message</strong> hidden in the URL — encoded so it's not obvious. Can you find and decode it?
      </div>

      <h2 style="margin-top: 20px;">📜 Server Access Log</h2>
      <div class="log-viewer"><%= logContent %></div>

      <div class="tools-section">
        <h3>🛠️ What to look for</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Scan for unusual URL parameters — anything that looks like a long random string</li>
          <li>It might be <strong>Base64</strong> encoded (letters + numbers, possibly ending in <code>=</code>)</li>
          <li>Search <strong>"Base64 decode online"</strong> to decode it!</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="hint-box">
        <details>
          <summary class="hint-toggle">💡 Need a hint?</summary>
          <p style="margin-top:8px;">Look at the <code>/search?q=</code> request from IP <code>10.0.0.55</code>. That long string after <code>q=</code> is Base64. Decode it!</p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="flag-form">
      <input type="text" class="flag-input" id="flagInput" placeholder="flag{...}" />
      <button class="submit-btn" onclick="submitFlag('ch5')">Submit Flag</button>
    </div>
    <div class="result-msg" id="result"></div>
  </div>
  <script src="/js/submit.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
